def clean_proglang_ever(row):
  langs = globals()['ever_langs']

  proglang_ever = row['proglang_ever']
  proglang_ever = [str.strip(lang) for lang in str.split(proglang_ever, ',')]
  
  proglang_ever = np.core.char.replace(proglang_ever, 'R (Programming Language)', 'R')
  proglang_ever = np.core.char.replace(proglang_ever, 'Rstudio', 'R')
  proglang_ever = np.core.char.replace(proglang_ever, 'Visual Studio/Visual Basic', 'Visual Basic')
  
  proglang_ever = np.unique(proglang_ever)

  proglang_ever = [lang for lang in proglang_ever if lang in langs]

  return proglang_ever

# Terdapat Visual Studio yang harusnya diganti Visual Basic
def clean_proglang_fav(row):
  langs = globals()['fav_langs']

  proglang_fav = row['proglang_fav']
  proglang_fav = [str.strip(lang) for lang in str.split(proglang_fav, ',')]
  
  proglang_fav = np.core.char.replace(proglang_fav, 'R  (Programming Language)', 'R')
  proglang_fav = np.core.char.replace(proglang_fav, 'Visual Studio', 'Visual Basic')
  
  proglang_fav = np.unique(proglang_fav)

  proglang_fav = [lang for lang in proglang_fav if lang in langs]

  return proglang_fav

def clean_text_edit_fav(row):
  editors = globals()['editors']

  text_edit_fav = row['text_edit_fav']
  text_edit_fav = [str.strip(editor) for editor in str.split(text_edit_fav, ',')]
  
  text_edit_fav = np.core.char.replace(text_edit_fav, 'Jupyter notebook', 'Jupyter Notebook (Google Collab)')
  text_edit_fav = np.core.char.replace(text_edit_fav, 'R-Studio', 'RStudio')
  text_edit_fav = np.core.char.replace(text_edit_fav, 'R Studio', 'RStudio')
  
  text_edit_fav = np.unique(text_edit_fav)

  text_edit_fav = [editor for editor in text_edit_fav if editor in editors]

  return text_edit_fav

def clean_mobapp_frm_fav(row):
  frameworks = globals()['mobapp_frm']

  mobapp_frm_fav = row['mobapp_frm_fav']
  mobapp_frm_fav = [str.strip(framework) for framework in str.split(mobapp_frm_fav, ',')]

  mobapp_frm_fav = np.unique(mobapp_frm_fav)

  mobapp_frm_fav = [framework for framework in mobapp_frm_fav if framework in frameworks]

  return mobapp_frm_fav

def clean_web_frm_fav(row):
  frameworks = globals()['web_frm']
  

  web_frm_fav = row['web_frm_fav']
  web_frm_fav = [str.strip(framework) for framework in str.split(web_frm_fav, ',')]

  web_frm_fav = np.core.char.replace(web_frm_fav, 'Tailwind CSS', 'Tailwind')
  
  web_frm_fav = np.unique(web_frm_fav)

  web_frm_fav = [framework for framework in web_frm_fav if framework in frameworks]

  return web_frm_fav

# Terdapat EViews
def clean_stattools_ever(row):
  stattools = globals()['stattools']


  stattools_ever = row['stattools_ever']
  stattools_ever = [str.strip(stattool) for stattool in str.split(stattools_ever, ',')]

  stattools_ever = np.core.char.replace(stattools_ever, 'Eviews', 'EViews')
  stattools_ever = np.core.char.replace(stattools_ever, 'Google Spreadsheet', 'Microsoft Excel')
  stattools_ever = np.core.char.replace(stattools_ever, 'Weka (Machine Learning)', 'Weka')
  stattools_ever = np.core.char.replace(stattools_ever, 'WinBugs (Simulasi Data)', 'WinBugs')
  stattools_ever = np.core.char.replace(stattools_ever, 'Python (Pandas', 'Python')

  stattools_ever = np.unique(stattools_ever)

  stattools_ever = [stattool for stattool in stattools_ever if stattool in stattools]

  return stattools_ever

def clean_forum(row):
  forums = globals()['forums']

  forum = row['forum']
  forum = [str.strip(frm) for frm in str.split(forum, ',')]
  
  forum = np.core.char.replace(forum, 'Komunitas di Facebook', 'Facebook')
  forum = np.core.char.replace(forum, 'Website Penn State Departement of Statistics Time Series', 'Penn State')
  forum = np.core.char.replace(forum, 'qastack', 'QAStack')
  forum = np.core.char.replace(forum, 'towardsdatascience', 'Towards Data Science')
  forum = np.core.char.replace(forum, 'datacamp', 'DataCamp')

  forum = np.unique(forum)

  forum = [frm if frm in forums else 'Others' for frm in forum ]

  return forum

def clean_focus_domain(row):
  domains = globals()['domains']

  focus_domain = row['focus_domain']

  focus_domain = str.replace(focus_domain, 'Artificial Intelligence / Machine Learning', 'Machine Learning')
  focus_domain = str.replace(focus_domain, 'AI', 'Machine Learning')
  focus_domain = str.replace(focus_domain, 'Machine Learning', 'Artificial Intelligence / Machine Learning')
  focus_domain = str.replace(focus_domain, 'Network engineer', 'Network Engineering')
  focus_domain = str.replace(focus_domain, 'Android Development', 'Mobile development')
  focus_domain = str.replace(focus_domain, 'desktop development', 'Desktop App Development')

  focus_domain = focus_domain if focus_domain in domains else 'Others'

  return focus_domain

def make_dumpy(values, ref_column, ref):

  df = pd.DataFrame(
      data = np.zeros((ref.shape[0],len(values))),
      columns = values,
      dtype = np.int8
  )

  df['email'] = ref['email']
  
  def fill_df(row):
    email = row['email']
    langs = ref.loc[ref['email'] == email, ref_column].reset_index(drop = True)[0]
    row[langs] = 1

    return row

  df = df.apply(fill_df, axis = 1)
  df['email'] = df['email'].astype('string')

  return df[['email'] + values]

def get_top(df):
  top = df.drop('email', 1).sum().sort_values(ascending = False)[                                                                
    df.drop('email', 1).sum().sort_values(ascending = False) > 0
  ]
  return top

# Mencari ranking dari dataframe dumpy yang sudah dibuat

def make_rank_fig(top_series, tidak_ada, title, color = None, savename = None, **save_kwargs) :
  
  plt.figure(figsize = (17,8))
  ax = top_series.sort_values().drop(tidak_ada).plot.barh(width = 0.95, color = color)

  for spine in ax.spines.values():
    spine.set_visible(False)
  
  dist = max([a.get_width() for a in ax.patches])/50
  for a in ax.patches:
    ax.text(
        a.get_width()+dist, a.get_y() + a.get_height() /2, 
        format(a.get_width() / top_series.sum() * 100, '.1f') + '%' ,
        va = 'center', ha = 'center', fontsize = 12
    ) 
  ax.set_title(title, size = 20)
  
  # plt.figure(figsize = (12,7))
  # ax = plt.barh(
  #     y = top_series.sort_values().drop(tidak_ada).index,
  #     width = top_series.sort_values().drop(tidak_ada).values,
  #     color = color
  # )

def make_likert_graph(data, likert_col, title_template, palette = 'magma', plot = sns.countplot, savename = None, **save_kwargs):
  fgrid = sns.FacetGrid(
      data, col = 'tingkat', 
      col_order = ['Tingkat 1', 'Tingkat 2', 'Tingkat 3', 'Tingkat 4'], 
      palette = palette, height = 5, margin_titles=True, col_wrap = 2
  )

  fgrid.map(plot, likert_col, order = ['0','1','2','3','4','5','6'], palette = palette)
  fgrid.set_xticklabels(['0','1','2','3','4','5','6'], rotation = 70, size = 12)
  fgrid.set_titles(col_template = title_template ,size = 15,)
  fgrid.set_xlabels('Skala')
  fgrid.tight_layout()

  if savename:
    fgrid.savefig(os.path.join(visdat_path, savename), **save_kwargs)

  plt.show()

def get_pct(row):
  sum_ = row.sum()
  pct_ = row / sum_

  return pct_
  
def get_expected_value(df):
  sum_bottom = df.sum().values.reshape(1,-1)
  sum_right = df.sum(axis = 1).values.reshape(-1,1)
  expected_value = pd.DataFrame(
      np.matmul(
          sum_right,
          sum_bottom
      ) / df.sum().sum(),
      columns = df.columns,
      index = df.index
  )

  return expected_value

def plot_cat(df, index_lab, column_lab, xlab = None, ylab = None, cmap_l = 'summer', cmap_r = 'autumn', savename = None, **save_kwargs):
  fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize = (14,7))

  df.apply(get_pct, axis = 1).plot(kind = 'bar', stacked = True, width = 0.9, ax = axs[0], cmap = cmap_l)
  df.apply(get_pct, axis = 0).transpose().plot(kind = 'bar', stacked = True, width = 0.9, ax = axs[1], cmap = cmap_r)
  axs[0].set_title("{} \nper\n {}".format(column_lab, index_lab), size = 15)
  axs[1].set_title("{} \nper\n {}".format(index_lab, column_lab), size = 15)
  
  if xlab:
    axs[0].set_xlabel(xlab[0])
    axs[1].set_xlabel(xlab[1])
  if ylab:
    axs[0].set_ylabel(ylab[0])
    axs[1].set_ylabel(ylab[1])
  if savename:
    fig.savefig(os.path.join(visdat_path, savename), **save_kwargs)

  # fig.tight_layout()
  fig.show()

def total_under_ev(df):
  total_under = df.applymap(lambda x : True if x < 5 else False).sum().sum()
  total_cell = df.shape[0] * df.shape[1]

  return '{} %'.format(total_under / total_cell * 100)

def get_0_values(df):
  return df.applymap(lambda x : True if x == 0 else False)

def save_xls(list_dfs, xls_path, names = None):
  from pandas import ExcelWriter

  with ExcelWriter(xls_path) as writer:
    if not names :
      for n, df in enumerate(list_dfs):
        df.to_excel(writer,'sheet%s' % n)
      writer.save()
    else :
      if len(names) != len(list_dfs):
        raise Exception("Panjang names harus sama dengan list_dfs")
      else :
        for df, name in zip(list_dfs, names):
          df.to_excel(writer, name, index = False)
